250 g Ground Beef
2 unit(s) Radish
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
7 g Black Sesame Seeds
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
2 unit(s) Green Onion
4 tbsp Soy Sauce Mirin Blend
2 tsp Sriracha
2 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
1.5 tsp Sugar*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce
Thinly slice radishes into rounds.
Thinly slice green onion.
In a small bowl, combine mayo, sriracha and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) soy sauce mirin blend. (TIP: This is your spicy mayo.)
In a large bowl, combine sesame oil, half the vinegar, and 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar. Add coleslaw mix and toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

To a small pot, add remaining vinegar, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) water and 1 tsp (2 tsp) sugar. Season with salt.
Bring to a simmer over medium-high. Cook for 1 min, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat, then add radishes.
Set aside to cool, stirring occasionally.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium.
Add sesame seeds to the dry pan. Toast for 3-4 min, stirring often, until golden. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)
Transfer to a plate.

Reheat the same pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef. Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up beef into smaller pieces until no pink remains.**
Carefully remove and discard excess fat, if you like.
Add remaining soy sauce mirin blend and stir to combine. Cook for 1-2 min, until sauce thickens slightly.
Remove from heat. Season with salt and pepper, if you like.

Just before serving, wrap tortillas in paper towels.
Microwave for 30 sec-1 min, until tortillas are warm and flexible. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm the tortillas!)

Drain pickled radishes, discarding brine.
Divide tortillas between plates.
Top with sesame slaw, beef and pickled radishes.
Top with spicy mayo, sesame seeds and green onions.